            The Government may have a commitment, but they are in danger of making life too complicated with too many different initiatives. If they really want to address
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_106wh' title='Col. 106WH &mdash; HC Deb 21 March 2001 vol 365 c106WH' name='column_106wh' href='#column_106wh' rel='bookmark'>106WH</a>
            the issues facing families, simplifying the tax system and easing the burden on the lower paid would be a far better way of doing so than too many, too complicated initiatives that not everyone understands.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
